title: Automatic Palette Switching
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

<<.from-version "5.5.0">> Some palettes switch their colours automatically in response to changes in their environment.

The core palette ''~AutoToggle'' follows the dark mode setting of the operating system. Select it in the [[Palette Chooser]] and the wiki will use a light palette when the operating system is in light mode, and a dark palette when it is in dark mode. The switch happens as soon as the operating system setting changes, and does not mark the wiki as having unsaved changes.

The light and dark palettes that ''~AutoToggle'' uses can themselves be chosen in the settings panel beneath the palette chooser.

The same mechanism lets palette authors respond to conditions other than dark mode. For example, a palette can define separate schemes for different times of day. See [[Colour Schemes]] for how such palettes are constructed.
